cluster_relations.rel_desc: Pollen is a reproductive material produced by flowers.
AI systems generate decisions whose reasoning can be hard to understand.

qualifiers.TemporalQualifier: as systems become more complex and opaque
qualifiers.OtherQualifier: ExplainabilityContext: challenging to understand the decision-making process

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject entity is generated or produced by the object entity.
args.justification: In this relation, 'pollen' (subject) is described as reproductive material produced by 'flowers' (object), so the predicate must capture that the subject is the product of the object. The passive-direction predicate 'is_produced_by' accurately reflects this direction.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject entity generates or produces the object entity as an output or result.
args.justification: In this relation, 'AI systems' (subject) generate 'AI system decisions' (object), matching an active-direction production predicate. Using 'produces' preserves this direction and aligns with standard production/output semantics.

Both relations describe a producer–product linkage: flowers producing pollen, and AI systems producing decisions. Despite opposite predicate direction in one case, they share the same conceptual family of a process or agent yielding an output.

In both cases, the producer causally leads to the existence of the product (pollen caused by flowers, decisions caused by AI systems). This is best captured as a causal/processual link rather than mere association.
